An elderly woman has died after falling from cliffs at a picturesque holiday spot. 

Police and emergency services were called to Porth Beach in Newquay, Cornwall, after the pensioner was found unconscious in a cave at 3.20pm yesterday.

The woman, said to be in her eighties and from the local area, is believed to have fallen from the cliffs above, near Whipsderry Beach.

