A spokesman for Devon and Cornwall Police said: 'Her next of kin have been informed and a file is now being prepared for the coroner.'

It is believed the woman had tumbled 20ft down a shaft into the cave and lay hidden from view until a man walking his dog on the beach spotted her. 

Officers said they are not looking for anyone else in connection with her death. 

 

 

